-- Saudi Arabia Looks at Boosting Local Consulting Firms, Eqtisadiah Reports
-- Mourad Haroutunian
-- 2010-07-07T06:10:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-07/saudi-arabia-looks-at-boosting-local-consulting-firms-eqtisadiah-reports.html

          
          
             Saudi Arabia is exploring ways to
raise local companies’ share of the market for consulting
services from the current 300 million riyals ($79.9 million), or
15 percent,  Al Eqtisadiah  reported, citing Assem Arab, a member
of the  Riyadh Chamber of Commerce and Industry .  
 Forty-five global and 6,000 Saudi consulting companies
compete in the kingdom’s 2 billion-riyal market, according to
the newspaper said.  
